# Documentation Standards — Mandatory

Every created or modified TypeScript/TSX file must have a TSDoc header at the top of the file.

## Required header

```typescript
/**
 * @module ModuleName
 * @description Brief description of the module purpose.
 * @packageDocumentation
 *
 * Key exports: ExportA, ExportB
 * Consumed by: @excalidraw/excalidraw
 * Part of: @excalidraw/math
 */
```

The block must include:
- `@module` — the module name
- `@description` — the module purpose
- `@packageDocumentation`
- Key exports
- Which package consumes this module
- Parent package relationship (e.g. "Part of @excalidraw/math")

## Completion check

Before finishing any task, verify every touched `.ts`/`.tsx` file has this header. If any is missing, add it. Do not skip this even if the user does not mention documentation.
